definitions: lacking in physical steadiness or balance; prone to falling or wobbling
showing rapid emotional changes or unpredictable behavior patterns in mood
prone to chemical decomposition or change; not maintaining molecular integrity
examples: The unstable ladder wobbled dangerously under his weight
She stood on unstable ground near the cliff edge
His unstable moods made everyone around him nervous
The patient showed unstable behavior after stopping medication
The unstable compound must be stored at very low temperatures
Unstable isotopes decay rapidly into other elements

definitions: not firm or securely fixed; liable to fall or shake when moved
lacking consistency or regularity in pattern, movement, or development over time
examples: Her unsteady hands spilled coffee on the documents
The elderly man walked with unsteady steps down the hall
The company showed unsteady growth throughout the difficult year
His unsteady performance made the coach consider replacement

definitions: unable to be stopped or prevented from continuing or succeeding despite obstacles
examples: The unstoppable force of the avalanche destroyed everything below
Once she sets her mind on something, she becomes unstoppable
The team's unstoppable momentum carried them to the championship
Technology's unstoppable advance continues to reshape our world

definitions: not organized according to a system, pattern, or formal arrangement of parts
examples: The unstructured interview allowed for more natural conversation flow
Children benefit from some unstructured playtime during the day
The unstructured data required extensive processing before analysis began
Their unstructured approach to problem-solving often yielded creative results

definitions: not supported or proven by evidence, facts, or reliable documentation
examples: The newspaper retracted the unsubstantiated claims about the politician
Police dismissed the unsubstantiated rumors spreading through social media
Her unsubstantiated allegations damaged his reputation unfairly
The theory remained unsubstantiated despite years of research attempts

definitions: not achieving the intended aim, goal, or desired outcome despite effort
examples: Their unsuccessful attempt to climb the mountain ended in retreat
She made several unsuccessful applications before finding a job
The unsuccessful candidate congratulated the winner graciously
Despite unsuccessful experiments, the scientist continued researching

definitions: not fitting or appropriate for a particular purpose, occasion, or person
examples: This movie contains unsuitable content for young children
The rocky terrain proved unsuitable for wheelchair access
His casual attire was unsuitable for the formal dinner
These shoes are unsuitable for hiking in wet conditions

definitions: not having the right qualities or characteristics for something or someone
examples: He felt unsuited to the demanding role of CEO
The delicate fabric is unsuited for machine washing
They realized they were unsuited as romantic partners
Her temperament was unsuited to working in customer service

definitions: not celebrated or praised despite deserving recognition for achievements or contributions
examples: The unsung heroes of the pandemic were hospital cleaning staff
Many unsung artists contributed to the city's cultural renaissance
She remained an unsung pioneer in her scientific field
The documentary highlighted unsung contributions to civil rights

definitions: not watched, controlled, or directed by someone in authority or charge
examples: Children should not be left unsupervised near the pool
The unsupervised learning algorithm discovered patterns independently
Unsupervised access to the internet poses risks for minors
Workers completed unsupervised tasks during the night shift

definitions: not provided with needed help, evidence, structural support, or backing
examples: The unsupported beam began to sag under the weight
She felt unsupported by her family during the crisis
His unsupported accusations led to a defamation lawsuit
The software runs on unsupported operating systems at risk

definitions: not feeling, showing, or inspiring confidence about something; doubtful or hesitant
examples: She felt unsure about accepting the job offer abroad
The students looked unsure when asked the difficult question
He remained unsure whether to trust the new information
I'm unsure of the exact date but it was sometime in June

definitions: better or greater than any other; not exceeded in quality or degree
examples: Her unsurpassed skill at negotiation won many difficult cases
The view from the mountain top was unsurpassed in beauty
His unsurpassed record still stands after twenty years
The restaurant offers unsurpassed service and exceptional cuisine

definitions: not causing surprise because it was expected or could be predicted
examples: The team's victory was unsurprising given their recent performance
It's unsurprising that prices rose during the shortage period
Her reaction was unsurprising to those who knew her well
The unsurprising results confirmed what researchers had suspected

definitions: not aware of the presence of danger or deceit; innocently trusting
examples: The scammer targeted unsuspecting elderly victims online
The unsuspecting tourists walked right into the trap
The cat crept up on its unsuspecting prey
Unsuspecting customers bought the counterfeit products unknowingly

definitions: not feeling, showing, or expressing sympathy, understanding, or compassion for others
examples: The unsympathetic judge showed no mercy during sentencing
Her unsympathetic response hurt more than the rejection itself
The boss was unsympathetic to requests for flexible working hours
Critics gave unsympathetic reviews to the experimental play

definitions: in a natural wild state; not domesticated, cultivated, or brought under control
examples: The untamed wilderness stretched for hundreds of miles
Her untamed hair blew wildly in the ocean breeze
The documentary captured the untamed beauty of the Arctic
His untamed spirit refused to conform to social expectations

definitions: not yet exploited, utilized, or made use of despite being available
examples: The region has vast untapped natural resources waiting for development
She recognized the untapped potential in the young athlete
The company discovered untapped markets in rural areas
There's untapped talent in communities often overlooked by recruiters

definitions: not able to be maintained, defended, or justified, especially of a position or view
examples: His untenable position forced him to resign from office
The theory became untenable after new evidence emerged
Rising costs made their business model untenable
She found herself in an untenable situation at work

definitions: not yet tried, proven, or subjected to testing or examination
examples: The untested vaccine required more clinical trials before approval
Young untested players joined the team for the season
This untested theory needs experimental validation
The untested waters made swimming dangerous for tourists

definitions: too unlikely, terrible, or shocking to be thought possible or acceptable
examples: Twenty years ago, smartphones would have seemed unthinkable
The unthinkable tragedy left the community in deep mourning
It's unthinkable that she would betray our trust
War between these allies was once considered unthinkable

definitions: not arranged neatly or kept in order; messy or disorganized
examples: His untidy desk was covered with papers and coffee cups
The children left the playroom in an untidy state
Her untidy handwriting was difficult to read
The untidy garden had weeds growing everywhere

definitions: not fastened or bound with string, rope, or similar material
examples: His untied shoelaces nearly caused him to trip
The untied boat drifted away from the dock
She left her hair untied, flowing freely down her back
The untied package spilled its contents on the floor

definitions: happening or done at an unsuitable time, especially occurring before the expected time
examples: His untimely death at age 35 shocked the community
The untimely frost destroyed most of the spring crops
An untimely interruption ruined the surprise announcement
The report's untimely release caused unnecessary panic

definitions: continuing to work or try with great energy and determination without becoming tired
examples: Her untiring efforts finally led to policy changes
The untiring volunteers worked through the night helping victims
He showed untiring dedication to his research for decades
The untiring campaigner never gave up fighting for justice

definitions: not having a title or name, especially of a work of art or document
examples: The artist left several untitled paintings in her studio
Save the untitled document before closing the program
The untitled manuscript was discovered in the author's desk
An untitled track appeared as a bonus on the album

definitions: too much or too many to be counted or measured accurately
not told or made known; kept secret or not revealed to others
examples: The war caused untold suffering to civilian populations
She possessed untold wealth from her inheritance
There are untold stories from that historical period
The untold truth finally emerged after decades of silence

definitions: unable to be affected, harmed, or defeated by outside forces
belonging to the lowest social class in traditional Hindu society; excluded from social contact
examples: The champion seemed untouchable after winning ten straight matches
Their untouchable lead in the market lasted for years
The untouchable caste faced centuries of discrimination
He was treated as untouchable after the scandal

definitions: not affected, changed, or damaged in any way by something
not handled, moved, or physically interfered with by anyone
examples: The ancient ruins remained untouched by modern development
Her spirit remained untouched by the harsh criticism
The crime scene was left untouched until investigators arrived
His dinner sat untouched on the table all evening

definitions: not having been trained or taught the skills for a particular job or activity
examples: Untrained workers pose safety risks in the factory
The untrained eye might miss these subtle details
An untrained voice can be damaged by improper singing
Untrained dogs often display behavioral problems

definitions: not given medical care, chemical processing, or other treatment
examples: Untreated infections can lead to serious complications
The untreated wood will rot if exposed to moisture
Untreated sewage polluted the river downstream
Her untreated anxiety worsened over the years

definitions: not in accordance with fact or reality; false or incorrect
examples: The rumors about their divorce were completely untrue
It's untrue that all teenagers are irresponsible
He made untrue statements during the investigation
The untrue allegations damaged her professional reputation

definitions: not able to be relied on as honest, truthful, or dependable
examples: The untrustworthy employee was caught stealing office supplies
Never share passwords with untrustworthy websites
His untrustworthy nature made maintaining friendships difficult
The untrustworthy narrator made the story more intriguing

definitions: not fit or able to be used for its intended purpose
examples: The damaged equipment was completely unusable
Heavy rain made the outdoor courts unusable
The corrupted file was unusable without data recovery
Poor translation made the instructions unusable

definitions: not put to use; available but not employed or utilized
examples: The unused tickets can be refunded within 30 days
An unused room became her home office
His unused vacation days accumulated over the years
The unused portion of the medicine should be discarded

definitions: not habitually or commonly occurring; different from what is typical or expected
examples: She has an unusual talent for remembering numbers
The unusual weather patterns concerned climate scientists
It's unusual for him to arrive late to meetings
The restaurant serves unusual combinations of flavors

definitions: not having received a vaccine to provide immunity against a disease
examples: Unvaccinated children cannot attend certain schools
The unvaccinated population remains vulnerable to infection
Travel restrictions apply to unvaccinated passengers
Unvaccinated pets pose health risks to other animals

definitions: having been revealed, disclosed, or made visible after being hidden
examples: The unveiled statue drew crowds to the town square
Her unveiled face showed her true emotions
The unveiled plans for development sparked community debate
The newly unveiled product exceeded market expectations

definitions: not confirmed as true or accurate through investigation or evidence
examples: The news outlet published unverified claims about the celebrity
Unverified users have limited access to platform features
Police warned against sharing unverified information online
The unverified report caused unnecessary alarm

definitions: not desired, wished for, or welcome; rejected or superfluous
examples: She received unwanted attention from her coworker
The shelter takes in unwanted pets from across the city
Unwanted emails filled his inbox every morning
The medicine caused unwanted side effects

definitions: not justified or authorized by the facts or circumstances; lacking adequate grounds
examples: His unwarranted criticism hurt team morale significantly
The police made an unwarranted search of her property
Such unwarranted optimism could lead to poor decisions
The unwarranted intrusion violated their privacy rights

definitions: steady and constant; not changing, weakening, or faltering in determination
examples: Her unwavering support helped him through difficult times
The soldier showed unwavering loyalty to his country
He maintained unwavering focus during the championship match
Their unwavering commitment to quality built customer trust

definitions: not married, especially when in a situation typically associated with marriage
examples: Support groups help unwed mothers navigate parenthood challenges
The unwed couple lived together for five years
In earlier times, unwed women faced social stigma
He remained unwed throughout his entire life

definitions: not wanted, invited, or giving pleasure; causing discomfort or displeasure
examples: The unwelcome guests stayed far longer than expected
Rain was an unwelcome surprise at the wedding
She received unwelcome news about her job application
His unwelcome advice only made the situation worse

definitions: not in good health; experiencing illness or physical discomfort
examples: She felt unwell and decided to leave work early
The unwell child stayed home from school
He's been unwell since eating at that restaurant
If you feel unwell, please consult your doctor

definitions: difficult to carry, move, or handle because of size, shape, weight, or complexity
examples: The unwieldy package barely fit through the doorway
She struggled with the unwieldy umbrella in strong wind
The unwieldy bureaucracy slowed decision-making processes
An unwieldy title made the book hard to remember

definitions: not ready, eager, or prepared to do something; reluctant or resistant
examples: He was unwilling to compromise on his principles
The unwilling participant had to be persuaded to join
She seemed unwilling to discuss her past experiences
The company was unwilling to invest in new technology

definitions: showing poor judgment or lack of wisdom; foolish or imprudent
examples: It was unwise to travel during the severe storm
His unwise investments cost him his retirement savings
Making promises you can't keep is unwise
The unwise decision haunted them for years afterward

definitions: not aware of the full facts or consequences; unintentional or inadvertent
examples: She was an unwitting accomplice to the fraud scheme
The tourists were unwitting victims of the overpricing scam
His unwitting mistake revealed the surprise party plans
They became unwitting participants in the social experiment

definitions: not capable of being put into practice successfully; impractical or unfeasible
examples: The proposed solution proved unworkable in practice
Budget constraints made the plan completely unworkable
Their unworkable agreement fell apart within weeks
The unworkable schedule caused stress for all employees
